<item>
            <title>[LU-16960] kmod-lustre-client package should include kernel version in release number</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16960</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The official package containing the kernel modules of the Lustre client for RHEL 9.2 is named kmod-lustre-client-2.15.3-1.el9.x86_64.rpm, so in case a rebuild is needed against a newer kernel version, the name would stay the same and the newer package wouldn&apos;t be an upgrade to the older version. &lt;br/&gt;
Instead, I propose the release number to be appended with the kernel version like it is done with the openafs package:&lt;br/&gt;
kmod-openafs-1.8.10-1.5.14.0_284.18.1.el9_2.x86_64.rpm&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL9</environment>
